review_blob: Great aroma - very malty/chocolatey. Not a lot of head and pretty light on in terms of carbonation. Drinks easily and quite reasonably balanced. Makes a good first up impression but feel it may be a bit of a one trick pony that will not be well served by repeated tastings.

Massive citrusy nose - subtle as a brick to the head! Nice amber orange colour, minimal head - a bit lifeless and heavy to look at.   Very bitter front of mouth, with a lot of length. Really benefits from some time in the glass to allow the very fruity characteristics to reveal themselves. Carries its high alcohol content pretty well, but as a 2012, would like to try it again some time in the future when I think it will be a better beer - clearly has the alcohol content and structure to keep for a good length of time.  Nice middle of the road palate - happily far more lively then it looks.

Nothing interesting in the nose. Decent head, nice cloudiness in a world of cold filtration!  Quite light, easy drinking and nicely balanced flavour and longish finish. A good session beer when you cant handle another lager!

sweet, malty nose. A generous creamy, caramel taste that goes down very easily. Far more subtle on the fruit/floral characters compared to a lot of pale ales I drink, but that is a good thing. Perhaps a touch lifeless for my taste. I guess its just very english (I mean that in a nice way!) and more a change up beer than something Id drink a lot of. But a very good beer nonetheless. Nice packaging too!

Hmmm... not sure how this qualifies as an East IPA.  My Kiwi mate refers to this as Mangatainoka Gold and claims its the beer that defines him! Unfortunately I find it a pretty bland, tepid and rather forgettable beer that might be worth a crack on a really hot day if it was ice cold, or for breakfast after a big night out. It is beer though, which is an undeniable  positive.

strong malty aroma. Big hops. Nice colour and head that doesnt overstay its welcome.  A dry, smokey finish with nice fruits. Aggressive character yet reasonably well balanced and carries its alcohol well. A very satisying beer. Not a fan of the Brooklyn Lager, but a big fan of this!
Pretty dull aroma and very frothy head but lots of front mouth flavour and pretty good length. A very enjoyable and almost surprisingly easy drinking IPA.
Above average ale. Easy to drink without being dull. Lot of head, although thats not a bad thing.
